.ue 1
                                                                       $.#$
                                                          Calw 5th Nov 1866
Dear Friedrich

.ue 2
                                                                       $.#$
Forts.: 5th Nov 1866
So you have a newborn in your house; Gross Mama will certainly come very
often to see to see how that grandson is growing with his mama, his papa
will very likely do like Mr. Weitbrecht who leaves his comptoire to look
after the boy. I thank you for looking a little after Christian Steiger;
perhaps this week, he may be permitted to return to Calw. How is it with
warm cloth do you feel the cold already?

Give my love to tante Caroline, tell her I am often with them in spirit!

tell Mama that I graduliere sie; Adieu dear Frederic
.fo -
                                Yours J.G.


                                                               <5 Nov 66>*
